7.00	The_Barefoot_Executive	The Barefoot Executive	The Barefoot Executive is a live-action Disney film released by Buena Vista Distribution in 1971 starring Kurt Russell, Joe Flynn, Wally Cox, Heather North and John Ritter (in his film debut), about a pet chimpanzee, named Raffles, who can predict the popularity of television programs. It was one of the "gimmick comedies" (geared towards children with a touch of adult humour for older viewers) Disney was known for in the 1960s and 1970s, and was frequently shown on the Wonderful World of Disney in the 1980s.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/74/Poster_of_the_movie_The_Barefoot_Executive.jpg/220px-Poster_of_the_movie_The_Barefoot_Executive.jpg
